quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  10,93,"And we established the people of Israel with a sure establishment, and we provided them with good things; nor did they disagree until there came to them the knowledge. Verily, thy Lord shall decide between them on the resurrection day concerning that whereon they did dispute"
  10,94,"And if thou art in doubt of that which we have sent down unto thee, ask those who read the Book before thee; verily, the truth is come to thee from thy Lord, be not then of those who are in doubt"
  10,95,"And be not of those who say the signs of God are lies, or thou wilt be of those who lose"
  10,96,"Verily, those against whom God's word is pronounced will not believe"
  10,97,"even though there come to them every sign, until they see the grievous woe"
  10,98,"Were it not so, a city would have believed and its faith would have profited it. But (none did) except the people of Jonas; when they believed we removed from them the torment of disgrace in this world, and we gave them provision for a while"
  10,99,"But had thy Lord pleased, all who are in the earth would have believed altogether; as for thee, wilt thou force men to become believers"
  10,100,It is not for any person to believe save by the permission of God; He puts horror on those who have no sense
  10,101,"Say, 'Behold what is in the heavens and in the earth! but signs and warners avail not a people who do not believe"
  10,102,"Do they await aught but the like of the days of those who passed away before them?' Say, 'Wait ye then! verily, I am with you one of those who wait"
  10,103,Then we will save our apostles and those who believe; thus is it due from us to save believers